OL,3,CWave of bus strikes threatened over
OL,4,Cpay and conditions
OL,6,FA series of nationwide strikes by bus
OL,7,Fdrivers is being threatened in
OL,8,Fdisputes over pay and conditions.
OL,10,FAround 7,500 members of Unite are
OL,11,Feither striking or balloting to take
OL,12,Findustrial action in areas including
OL,13,FBirkenhead, Brighton, Bristol,
OL,14,FCardiff, Chorley, London, Manchester,
OL,15,FNewcastle, Preston, Stoke and Swindon.
OL,17,FStrikes involving 450 Cardiff Bus
OL,18,Fworkers, 2,000 London United workers
OL,19,Fin West London, 550 First workers in
OL,20,FBristol and 70 Go South West workers
OL,21,Fin Swindon have already been announced.
